procedure.StepOne: Pat steaks dry and Season generously.
procedure.StepTwo: Pre-Heat a skillet over HIGH heat. Add Canola Oil and heat until extremely hot.
procedure.StepThree: Place Steaks on pan and sear for 3 minutes. DO NOT TOUCH. Flip and Sear for another 2-3 minutes. We want a deep brown crust.
procedure.StepFour: Lower the heat! Add the butter, thyme or rosemary, and the garlic. BUTTER BASTE!
procedure.StepFive: Use a thermometer to take the steaks off at 135F. SERVE!

name: Fried Chicken
ingredients: Lawry's Seasoning Salt, Garlic Powder, Cayenne Pepper

procedure.StepOne: Brine the Chicken! In a large mixing bowl, combine 10 cups of water, seasoning salt, garlic powder, and cayenne. Add chicken and refigerate for at least 4 Hours
procedure.StepTwo: Fill up a pot with 6 inches of oil and heat over Medium-High Heat. 365-380F.
procedure.StepThree: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour,seasoning salt, cayenne, and garlic powder. Remove chicken from brine and toss them in the flour mixture a few at a time.
procedure.StepFour: Once the oil is ready, drop in the coated chicken ONE AT A TIME. Drumsticks for 14 minutes and Thighs for 16 minutes. SERVE!

procedure.StepOne: Cook pasta al dente, around 7 minutes. Save 1 cup of Pasta Water.
procedure.StepTwo: In a saucepan, heat olive oil under medium heat. Once hot, toast the Black Pepper.
procedure.StepThree: Add One Cup of Pasta Water and let it simmer. Add the Spaghetti. MIX.
procedure.StepFour: Add Both the Cheeses and MIX MIX MIX. SERVE!

procedure.StepOne: Cook pasta al dente, around 7 minutes. Save 1 cup of Pasta Water.
procedure.StepTwo: In a skillet, add Diced Pancetta or Bacon. Cook on medium heat until fat renders out and meat is browned and crispy. Remove from heat.
procedure.StepThree: Add Pasta to Pan and MIX MIX MIX.
procedure.StepFour: Add Egg Yolks and Both Cheeses. TOSS TOSS TOSS. SERVE!

procedure.StepOne: Portion the Ground Beef into even balls and head a large skillet over Medium-High Heat.
procedure.StepTwo: Place Ground Beef Balls in the skillet and SMASH them with a spatula to form flat patties. (1/2 inch thick)
procedure.StepThree: Season top of patties to taste with seasonsings of choice. Sear Patties until there is a nice crust. (3-4 Minutes.) FLIP & REPEAT.
procedure.StepFour: Add Two slices of cheese on top of each patty and let it melt.
procedure.StepFive: Spread the butter over the Burger Buns and toast on a pan!

procedure.StepOne: Place Cheese on Bread and Close!
procedure.StepTwo: Butter the outside of the bread.
procedure.StepThree: Place sandwich on a cold pan over medium heat! Cook until bottom is golden brown! (2 to 4 minutes) FLIP!
procedure.StepFour: Toast the other side until it is golden brown and the cheese fully melts. SERVE!

procedure.StepOne: Dry the Filets and Season! Pre-Heat a Pan over High Heat.
procedure.StepTwo: Oil the Pan and Place Filets SKIN SIDE DOWN. If skin starts to curl, push filet down with a spatula.
procedure.StepThree: Sear the fish until skin crispy and fish 50% cooked, 2 to 3 minutes. FLIP!
procedure.StepFive: Add the butter and butter baste! SERVE!!

procedure.StepOne: Remove meat from Steamed Lobster and Cut into Bite-Sized Chunks.
procedure.StepTwo: In a Medium Bowl, mix mayonnaise, lemon zest & juice, chives, dill, and salt&pepper to taste. Add Lobster Chunks to mayo mixture.
procedure.StepThree: Butter Buns and Toast! Stuff Buns with Lobster Mixture and SERVE!

procedure.StepOne: Mash Avocado and Season to taste! Add Diced Red Onion and Chopped Cilantro.
procedure.StepTwo: Toast the Bread and Spread the Avocado Mixture!
procedure.StepThree: OPTIONAL! Fry up an Egg Over-Easy or Sunny-Side Up and top it off!

procedure.StepOne: In a mixing bowl, MASH the banana. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix!
procedure.StepTwo: Transfer and Split into Mason Jars! Ready to serve! I like to add fresh fruit (Berries or Banana) or some Granola!
